    "updated_at": "2015-09-10T03:31:28Z",
    "body": "Just tested in chrome 45.0.2454.85 and canary 47.0.2505.0 setting the `chrome://flags` and experienced the same issue (normal scrollbars work as expected in all browsers), so I'll try to create a minimum example and report it to the Chromium tracker.\n\nOne thing I've noticed though is that Chrome does indeed have a lighter border around the overlay scrollbars (and they are slightly thicker) making them more visible, is there any way to force electron to do the same?\n\n![scroll](https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/4189262/9779534/796b2336-5774-11e5-82d1-3eadaacccbc8.png)\n"
