    "created_at": "2015-09-10T03:52:35Z",
    "updated_at": "2015-09-10T03:53:34Z",
    "body": "No, both Chrome 45.0.2454.85 (32 bit) and Canary 47.0.2505.0 (64 bit) have the same scrollbars. I'm also using electron 0.32.1 today, which has the v45 engine, and the electron scrollbars are the same as in my original post.\n\nThis might be a very long shot, but could it be that Chrome detects the touch screen in my laptop and increases the scrollbars for touch, and somehow electron does not?\n"
